# Phase 14: Senior UI/UX Audit & Brand Pivot

Escaping the "YouTube clone" shadow by establishing a unique, professional visual language for VibeStream. Conducted via 7-agent design audit (Layout, Accessibility, Brand, Performance, Creator UX, Admin UX, and Mobile).

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Branding Pivot**: All Red (#DC2626) elements will be replaced with our signature Amber/Gold (#FFB800) to avoid trademark infringement and establish brand identity.
>
> **Interaction Fix**: The central play button overlay will be made fully interactive to ensure intuitive playback.

## Proposed Changes

### UI: Visual Identity & Icons
#### [MODIFY] [VideoPlayer.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/components/VideoPlayer.tsx)
- **Play Button**: Change central overlay icon from Red/White to a Glassmorphic Gold/Black aesthetic.
- **Scrubber**: Update progress bar from Red to Gold.
- **Interactions**: Ensure the central overlay handles click events directly to fix the "one button only" bug.

### Studio: Professional Dashboard Refinement
#### [MODIFY] [DashboardClient.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/app/studio/dashboard/DashboardClient.tsx)
- **Responsiveness**: Audit and fix grid layouts for 390px (Mobile) and 1440px (Desktop).
- **Typography**: Switch to more professional weights and spacing for data-heavy views.

### Admin: High-Fidelity UI
#### [MODIFY] [Admin-related-files]
- Review and polish the Admin Panel for a "SaaS-grade" professional feel.
- Ensure all metrics cards are responsive and use consistent branding.

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
- Click EXACTLY on the central play button to start/stop video.
- Verify NO red icons remain in the video player.
- Test dashboard on mobile dev tools (iPhone 12/13/14).
